article.headline: Oral Roberts 86, IUPUI 76
article.story: TULSA, Okla. (AP) -- Larry Owens had 21 points and nine rebounds to lead Oral Roberts past Indiana-University-Purdue University at Indianapolis 86-76 Saturday night. Caleb Green scored 18 points for Oral Roberts and Jonathan Bluitt added 15 points and nine assists for ORU (9-8, 4-1 Mid-Continent Conference), which shot a season-high 69 percent from the field (29-of-42). George Hill scored 22 of his game-high 26 points in the second half for the Jaguars (9-7, 4-1). Brandon Cameron added 17 points and Brandon Cole scored 16 for IUPUI, which was 48 percent from the field (28-of-59). Chris Riouse scored 12 of his 13 points in the first half to help ORU take a 43-32 lead into intermission. Riouse was 4-of-4 on 3-pointers during the first half. Green had eight points in the first eight minutes of the second half as ORU stretched its lead to 62-40. "For the first 35 minutes, that's as well as we've played in a long time," ORU coach Scott Sutton said. IUPUI went on a 9-0 run to cut its deficit to 72-60 with 4:57 left. A basket by Hill reduced the Golden Eagles lead to 80-72 with 1:20 remaining, but IUPUI could not get any closer. The Jaguars, who were outrebounded 25-23, lost for the second time in their last eight games. "We lost the game in the first half," IUPUI coach Ron Hunter said. "We made adjustments and came back in the second half, but just ran out of time."
